The paper discusses a method for approximating Bayesian inference, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves combining rejection sampling with particle filtering, which are both commonly used in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses tracking time-dependent parameters in online settings, which is a common topic in control systems (cs.SY). The paper provides numerical examples of the method applied to MNIST classification problems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the method, which is a common topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
